description:
The Crow in Tokyo. The Crow searching for the stolen soul of his lost love-the search taking him on a blood-red trail of vengeance. In order to set her free, the Crow must now do important things, like descend into the layered hell of Japanese Buddhist mythology. Then he must find the living body of his beloved... and kill it. The Crow's return concludes in explosive fashion here!

Note: This issue was released digitally one week before the print release.

  • Digital release date: November 21, 2012
  • Print release date: November 28, 2012
name: Chapter Five: There Are Many Hells

description: The annual anthology companion to the 2000 Small Press Expo.
name: Small Press Expo 2000

description: Unknown Quantities is a one-shot benefit anthology commemorating the 1999 March of Americas benefitting the Kensington Welfare Rights Union. Features the work of over 40 talents including: Alex Ross, Neil Gaiman, Rick Veitch, and Alan Moore.
name: Unknown Quantities

description: The Action Bible is a full graphically novelized version of the New Testament of Jesus Christ. It is a work that Sergio Cariello considers to be career defining and meaningful to his faith. It's realism in art along with scripture attract the attention of Christians and lovers of an epic story alike.
name: God's Redemptive Story

description:
Professor Ernst Kleist has achieved the impossible: he has genetically engineered powerful, obedient Aliens. When an operative from the funding organization is sent to do a routine check up, he finds Kleist's methods to be... unorthodox. "There is an adage," says Kleist, "about omelettes... and breaking eggs." The horror of nature is dwarfed by the terror of the man toying with it!

Ian Edginton weaves a complex tale of a man driven to harness nature's most violent creature, and the horrors involved with what he must become to achieve his goal. The terror is exquisitely illustrated by Will Simpson in what proved to be the most harrowing Aliens tale yet. Brace yourself for the collected Aliens: Rogue!
name: TPB

description:
Collects Fallen Son: Death of Captain America - Wolverine, Avengers, Captain America, Spider-Man, Iron Man. Where were you when Captain America died? Follow the reaction of the legendary heroes' best friends and closest comrades as they struggle to work through the emotions stirred by the loss of their ally, and the stages of grief that make them confront the part they may have played in that loss: Wolverine. The Avengers. Hawkeye. Spider-Man. Iron Man.

The death of Captain America hits the Marvel Universe - hard! Be there as superstar Jeph Loeb teams with the industry's top artists on a story that will have everyone talking, navigating the turbulent post-Civil War landscape! Can the world accept the death of a true hero? In the wake of a tragedy, we visit the top heroes of the Marvel Universe. How do people with amazing powers face a force that no one can fight? Is more violence coming? Featuring Wolverine, the Mighty Avengers, the New Avengers, Spider-Man and Iron Man!
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Fallen Son: The Death of Captain America

description: Join the adventuring rogue Kev and his companions Domato and Dindil as they greedily explore Tony Moseley's treacherous and hilarious world of Zogonia! Delve dungeons filled with ravenous beasts, deadly traps, and even deadlier companions in this side-splitting collection of one of Dragon magazine's most popular cartoons! Zogonia: Slice of Death contains 64 pages of comic strips, old and new, collected from the pages of Dragon. It also features an introduction by Tony Moseley revealing the artist's overview of the series.
name: Slice of Death

description:
If you're looking for cool cars, red-hot racing and awesome action, check out Totally...Hot Wheels™ #9 magazine!

Under The Hood

Fast cars look cool, but have you ever wondered what makes them work? Take a look under the skin of the Retro-Funk and discover the highly charged systems of one of the world’s fastest electric racers!

Hot Wheels World Records

Team Hot Wheels is the worlds greatest stunt team, but how did they do when faced with their craziest challenge so far?

Adventure Sports!

Bored of football? Tired of tennis? Had enough of hockey? Then take a look at these X-TREME sports! You won't find a better adventure anywhere else!

Hot Wheels Versus

We all know that Hot Wheels cars are awesome - but how do they stand up against each other? It's up to YOU to decide which is the best car from the ones below!

Rad Reviews

Check out some totally awesome things heading your way! Including a brand new video game, hot hoodies and F1 action!

Plus:

Check out the totally cool Hot Wheels™ prizes up for grabs this issue! Win an awesome Hot Wheels™ Wall Tracks Power Tower, Hot Wheels™ Mega Loop Mayhem Track Set, Hot Wheels Racer Zipbin Backpack and Odeon Cinema Tickets for you and your mates!

Mind-bending Hot Wheels™ puzzles & games

Massive Motors: take a look at these awesome vehicles and give each of them a rating out of 10!

Two pull-out posters

Fan Zone: the page all about you! Send in your photos/letters/creations
name: Hot Wheels #9

description:
The Madagascar gang are back for an all-new adventure! Run away to the circus with Marty, Melman, Gloria and Alex and pick up the ultimate guide to the new movie on your way! Plus there's a FREE Mega Grabber!

Madagascar Comic Strip - Long Live the King!

Watch out Monte Carlo, the Penguins are in town! Skipper and the rest of the gang have been enjoying the high life since they left Africa, but now they're planning the party to end all parties, with a little help from chimps and the mysterious King of Versailles. Can they stop Alex, Marty, Gloria and Melman crashing the scene and running away with their fun? There's only one way to find out!

Meet the Gang!

Meet the Madagascar Gang! All your favourite characters are back for the new movie adventure, including Alex, Marty, Melman and Gloria - plus their new circus friends!

Lots of Fun and Games!

Totally... Madagascar is full of loads of fun games, puzzles and activities! Pull-out and play the fantastic circus boardgame, cut out the penguins for a great pick-up game with your free grabber and there's an awesome cut out and keep afro-polkadot wig - just like Marty's!

Plus:

Win hilarious Madagascar books!

Madagascar puzzles & games
name: Madagascar 3

description:
This winter a group of heroes must come together to protect the hopes, beliefs and imaginations of every child on earth. They’ll have to use their amazing abilities to defeat an evil spirit and stop the fear and darkness that threatens the world. Let the battle commence…The Guardians are ready to rise!

Join in with the quest on sale now at all good retailers.

Guardians Unite!

We introduce you to the Guardians: North, Tooth Fairy, Bunnymund, Sandman, and Jack Frost. Find out about their extraordinary abilities, which they use to protect the planet! We also introduce you to the evil enemy, Pitch, who is working on a plan to change the world for the worse.

Brrrrriliant Boardgame!

Jack has used his weather powers to create a wild obstacle course. Which one of them will find their way through it and get back to the North Pole first?

Pitches Nightmares

Pitch wants children to be scared of him, so he hides under their beds at night to give them nightmares. In fact, he wants everyone to be scared of everything! We name the list of Pitch’s top ten funny phobias…

Plus:

’Friends like these’ comic strip!

Take part in the competition to win a cool prize!

Lots of arctic activities!
name: Rise of the Guardians

description:
Inside this issue:

Batman and Robin: Knightmoves

Bruce and his son, Damian, Batman and Robin, are being stalked by the murderous Nobody, a man from Bruce’s shared past who prefers to put criminals in the ground over putting them in prison!

First printed in Batman and Robin #3

Batman and Robin: Matter of Trust

How does Nobody know so much about Batman and Robin? Who is he? Why is he obsessed with Batman, Incorporated and the methods of the Dark Knight?

First printed in Batman and Robin #2

Batman: Attack on Wayne Manor

The Owls have ruled Gotham from the shadows for centuries, using their deathless Talons to strike terror into the heart of the rich and powerful. As Batman, Bruce could not prevail against them… how can he hope to survive when the Talons invade his home?

First printed in Batman #8

Inside this issue:

BATMAN AND ROBIN – MUTINEER

Discover the deadly connection between Bruce Wayne and the man who calls himself Nobody – and watch as Damien spirals down into out and out mutiny!

First printed in Batman and Robin #5

BATMAN – THE CALL

With an armoured battlesuit on his side, can Batman turn the tide against the Talons in his cave? Meanwhile, Alfred puts out the call to the entire Bat-family!

First printed in Batman and Robin #8

BATMAN – NIGHT OF THE OWLS

The conflict is here at last. Plus, in the first part of ‘THE FALL OF THE HOUSE OF WAYNE’, discover that dark secret that Jarvis Pennyworth, first butler to the Waynes, took to his grave!

First printed in Batman #9

Inside this issue:

BATMAN AND ROBIN – THE REAL ME

Is Damian really going to betray the trust put in him by his father, Bruce Wayne? Has the deadly Nobody really managed to twist him that much? What can Batman do to prevent his son slipping further away?

First printed in Batman and Robin #6

BATMAN – ASSAULT ON THE COURT

With the Talons defeated, however temporarily, Batman decides the time has come to take the fight to the Court of Owls... starting by hitting them where it hurts the most!

First printed in Batman and Robin #10

BATMAN – MY BROTHER'S KEEPER

After the shocking revelations in the last chapter, what more can Bruce Wayne do to reclaim his stolen history and his city from the Court of Owls? It all goes down here!

First printed in Batman #9

Batman™ & Aquaman in 'Under The Sea' Part Two

Previously in Batman™: The Brave and the Bold... BATMAN and Aquaman fought the fiendish Fisherman and his pirate crew, but were rescued by Captain Fear and his ghost ship. On a quest for the Amulet of Arion, which could break Fear's curse they were attacked by a giant sea monster! This issue, will they succeed in their mission?

Episode Guide: 'Mayhem of the Music Meister'

Revisit this musical spectacular, as the evil Music Meister uses his singing voice to hypnotise heroes and villains alike to control them!

Evil Under The Sea

A splash-fest of aquatic themed puzzles and challenges for landlubbers and sea dogs!

The Batman™ Secret Files: The Fiddler

He may not look dangerous, but beneath that innocuous exterior is a musical maniac set on unleashing a concerto of chaos! Read The Fiddler's secret files and find out all you need to know about the malevolent maestro.

Also inside this issue:

Win LEGO® Series 7 Minifigures!

Cut out and make a Dark Knight Dare Dice!

See if your letter, drawing or picture has been included in Bat Signals!

Puzzle over Blue Beetle's Brain Busters!

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
Where were you when Captain America died? Perhaps you were listening to the radio or reading the morning paper. Maybe you were surfing the web or on the phone with a friend. You were probably shocked, most likely thinking, 'How could this happen to Cap?' And for a moment, you perhaps thought about all the ways the super soldier meant something to you. Something very real, very abiding. Fallen Son: Death of Captain America follows the reaction of the legendary heroes' best friends and closest comrades as they struggle to work through the emotions stirred by the loss of their ally, and the stages of grief that make them confront the part they may have played in that loss. This is their story. This is Cap's story. This is our story. The story of a Fallen Son and the world he helped make a better place. Plus, this edition also includes tons of never-before-seen extras!

Collecting FALLEN SON: WOLVERINE, AVENGERS, CAPTAIN AMERICA, SPIDER-MAN and IRON MAN; and CAPTAIN AMERICA COMICS #1 plus extras from MARVEL SPOTLIGHT: CAPTAIN AMERICA REMEMBERED and the OFFICIAL HANDBOOK OF THE MARVEL UNIVERSE.
name: HC

volume.name: Fallen Son: The Death of Captain America Oversized Edition

description: The Batman barely survived his last encounter with the alien hunter from beyond the stars. Now, the Predator has returned to Gotham and he is not alone. A bounty has been placed on the Dark Knight Detective's head and every assassin and hired gun in the criminal underworld wants to cash in. Unfortunately for them, the Predator is not in the habit of sharing his prey. Luckily, Batman is not alone either. He'll get some much needed assistance from the Huntress, nut will it be enough. It's Batman vs. the Predator: Round 2.
name: TPB

description: Contains : Astonishing X-Men (2004) #43-47

In Northam, members of the rich and elite are conducting illegal hunts and taking trophies from their conquered prey. One such trophy is an X-O helmet stolen from a Predator. Now, the Predator has come to Northam to take the trophy back by any means necessary. When the carnage begins, it's up to Magnus Robot Fighter to make sure the good guys win. Just one question: who are the good guys?

Reprints Predator vs. Magnus Robot Fighter #1 & 2.
